  Appendix 2  7 

ADB Loans and Technical Assistance (TA) to Develop Capital Markets in Southeast Asia 

A.  Loans 
•  ADB. 1988. Report and Recommendation of the President to the Board of Directors on Proposed 
Loans to The Republic of Indonesia for the Financial Sector Program. Manila (Loans 938/939); 
•  ADB. 1992. Report and Recommendation of the President to the Board of Directors on a 
Proposed Loan to The Republic of Indonesia for the Second Financial Sector Program. Manila 
(Loan 1160);  
•  ADB. 1998. Report and Recommendation of the President to the Board of Directors on a 
Proposed Loan to The Republic of Indonesia for Financial Governance Reforms. Manila (Loan 
1618);  
•  ADB.  1995.  Report  and  Recommendations  of  the  President  to  the  Board  of  Directors  on 
Proposed Loan to Philippines for Capital Market Development Program. Manila (Loan 1363);  
•  ADB. 2001. Report and Recommendation of the President to the Board of Directors on a 
Proposed Loan to the Republic of the Philippines for Nonbank Financial Governance Program. 
Manila (Loan 1858);  
•  ADB. 2003. Report and Recommendation of the President to the Board of Directors on a 
Proposed Loan to The Republic of the Philippines for the Second Nonbank Financial Governance 
Program. Manila (Loan 2003); 
•  ADB. 1997. Report and Recommendation of the President to the Board of Directors on a 
Proposed Loan to The Kingdom of Thailand for the Financial Markets Reform Program. Manila 
(Loan 1600). 

B.  Country-specific TA 
•  ADB. 2000. Technical Assistance to The Republic of Indonesia for Development of Financial 
Services Supervisory Institution. Manila (TA 3620) for $1.7 million;  
•  ADB. 2002. Technical Assistance to The Republic of Indonesia for Establishment of Financial 
Services Authority. Manila (TA 3850) for $1.195 million;  
•  ADB. 1995. Technical Assistance to Philippines for Capital Market Development. Manila (2379) 
for $250,000;  
•  ADB. 1999. Technical Assistance to The Republic of the Philippines for Nonbank Financial Sector 
Development. Manila (TA 3245) for $2 million;  
•  ADB.  2001.  Technical  Assistance  to  Philippines  for  Strengthening  Regulatory  and  Market 
Governance. Manila (TA 3773) for $1 million; 
•  ADB. 2003. Technical Assistance to The Republic of the Philippines for Support of Nonbank 
Financial Governance II.  Manila (TA 4168) for $500,000;  
•  ADB.  2004.  Technical  Assistance  to  The  Republic  of  the  Philippines  for  Strengthening 
Governance of Securities Trading Markets. Manila (TA 4321) for $250,000;  
•  ADB. 1997. Technical Assistance to Malaysia for Capital Market Development. Manila (1815) for 
$250,000; 
•  ADB.  1997.  Technical  Assistance  to  Thailand  for  Strengthening  Information  Disclosure  and 
Compliance. Manila (2956) for $1.150 million;  
•  ADB. 1997. Technical Assistance to The Kingdom of Thailand for Asset Securitization. Manila 
(TA 2957) for $1.150 million. 

C.  Regional TA 
•  ADB. 1997. Technical Assistance for Collaborative Initiatives of Capital and Financial Market 
Development. Manila (TA 5763-REG) for $900,000; 
•  ADB. 1998. Technical Assistance for Study on Development of Government Bond Markets. 
Manila (TA 5809-REG) for $$740,000;  
•  ADB. 2001. Technical Assistance for Study on Asian Financial Markets. Manila (TA 5985- REG) 
for $750,000;  
•  ADB.1997. Technical Assistance for ASEAN + 3 Regional Guarantee Mechanism. Manila (TA 
6127-REG) for $1,000,000;  
•  ADB. 2005. Technical Assistance for ASEAN + 3 Asian Bond Market Initiative. (TA 6244-REG) 
for $400,000;  
•  ADB. 2004. Technical Assistance for Asian Bonds Online.  (Japan Fund for Information and 
Communication Technology) for $2,000,000.
